-- Russia Spy Chief’s Son to Oversee Privatization, Kommersant Says
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2012-08-15T04:26:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-15/russia-spy-chief-s-son-to-oversee-privatization-kommersant-says.html
Pavel Fradkov, the younger son of
Russia’s Foreign Intellingence Chief,  Mikhail Fradkov , may
become deputy head of the Federal Property Agency, which
organizes state asset sales,  Kommersant  said, citing
unidentified people familiar with the matter.  Olga Dergunova, a former country head of Microsoft Corp.,
was appointed to lead the agency in June and is now forming her
team, according to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
